Case Study : Project SafeCity – Urban
Public Safety Analytics Platform
SafeCity Technologies operates a large-scale public safety platform that integrates data from
surveillance cameras, emergency response systems, law enforcement databases, traffic
management systems, and IoT-enabled city infrastructure. The platform supports public safety
agencies responsible for crime prevention, incident response, disaster management, and
emergency coordination across major metropolitan areas. As urban populations continue to
grow, the volume of real-time video feeds, sensor data, and operational events processed by
the platform has increased significantly.
Several recent incidents involving communication delays, infrastructure failures, and system
outages have raised concerns regarding operational resilience and response effectiveness.
Existing infrastructure lacks sufficient automation, observability, and disaster recovery
capabilities to support mission-critical operations. Government authorities have approved a
modernization initiative to create a cloud-native platform capable of delivering real-time
analytics, predictive threat detection, and highly available public safety services.
As the lead DevOps engineering team, your challenge is to design and implement a resilient
DevOps ecosystem capable of processing millions of events per minute while maintaining
operational continuity. Applications must be containerized using Docker, infrastructure
provisioned using Terraform, deployments orchestrated through Kubernetes, and CI/CD
pipelines automated using Jenkins. Monitoring and logging must be implemented using
Prometheus, Grafana, and ELK Stack, while Vault secures critical credentials and system
secrets. During evaluation, city authorities may simulate infrastructure outages, communication
failures, cyberattacks, emergency traffic surges, and data center disruptions. The platform must
demonstrate self-healing, fault tolerance, and uninterrupted operations.
Objective: The objective of this project is to design, implement, and demonstrate a highly
available DevOps platform supporting public safety analytics, infrastructure automation,
operational monitoring, and disaster recovery.

Main Deliverables and Expected Outcomes

Design, develop, and deploy a complete production-ready business application, dashboard, API platform, monitoring platform, analytics system, or management portal based on the given problem statement. The solution must demonstrate a comprehensive DevOps implementation, including:

Dockerized application and supporting services
Infrastructure provisioning and automation using Terraform
Kubernetes-based container orchestration and deployment
CI/CD pipelines implemented with Jenkins
Monitoring, alerting, and observability systems
Centralized logging and log management
Secure secrets and configuration management
Backup, disaster recovery, and business continuity procedures
Architecture design and technical documentation
High availability, scalability, security, resilience, and operational readiness best practices

The final deliverable should showcase an end-to-end cloud-native platform that is fully automated, deployable, maintainable, and capable of supporting real-world production workloads.

